                  <div class="flex-fill">
                     <h2>WHAT IS A FLAVOR POWDER?</h2>
                     <p>A flavor powder is ideal for flavoring products that must be kept dry. For example, you can use flavoring powders to flavor dry pancake mixes, protein powders, and instant mixes. Flavor powders dissolve readily in warm water and work well for mixes with an extended shelf life. To get the most out of your flavoring powders when baking, use them for a shorter cooking time.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
               <div class="block d-flex flex-wrap">
                  <div class="flex-fill">
                     <h2>USAGE GUIDELINES FOR FLAVORING POWDERS:</h2>
                     <p>Flavor powders are fairly weak compared to other flavors. Starting usage would be around .25% to 1% by weight of total ingredients and even up to 5% depending on the application. When adding the flavoring powder to the recipe, mix it in with dry ingredients so that it combines properly.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
               <div class="block d-flex flex-wrap">
                  <div class="flex-fill">
                     <h2>HOW TO USE POWDERED FLAVORINGS:</h2>
                     <p>Flavor powders are perfect for adding to dry mixes and are even used in some old-school baking applications. Flavoring powders can be sprinkled on top of food to spice or season your dishes, enhancing the flavor of the food. Some of the best applications for flavor powders are:</p>
                     <ul>
                        <li>Smoothies</li>
                        <li>Baked goods</li>
                        <li>Dry mixes</li>
                        <li>Shakes</li>
                        <li>Rubs</li>
                        <li>Popcorn</li>
                        <li>Seasoning for vegetables</li>
                        <li>Bread</li>
                        <li>Marinades</li>
                        <li>Sauces</li>
                        <li>Maintaining a pre-made mix for months to come</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>Flavoring powders are excellent for dry food applications and can be used as a replacement for liquid flavorings to boost the flavor of your food.</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
