               <div class="attention-note">
                  <h2>OVER FLAVORING YOUR PRODUCT WITH FLAVOR POWDERS</h2>
                  <p>You’ll know that you’ve over-flavored your food if you taste a medicinal or minty taste on your palate. Another sign that you have over-flavored your culinary creation is that you are burping the flavor up over an hour after consuming the food. The key to enhancing the flavor of your baked good or beverage with flavor powders and not over-flavoring it is to use just enough flavor powder so you tease the taste buds. Doing so will make the food or drink delectable, and people will want to eat or drink more of the food or beverage.</p>
